<TITLE> BNP yet to select deputy leader of opposition </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)The main opposition BNP has yet to select opposition leader Khaleda Zia's deputy in parliament. The second meeting of the BNP parliamentary party (BNPP) was chaired by Khaleda on Sunday afternoon. "We have selected the Joynal Abdin Faruk as the chief whip of the opposition, but the deputy leader of the opposition is yet to be selected," Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury told bdnews24.com in parliament. The ruling BNP, during its five-year tenure of the last parliament, but could not select a deputy leader of the House either. The BNPP nominated Khaleda Zia and MK Anwar as its representatives to the Privilege Committee, ABM Ashraf Uddin Nizan told bdnews24.com. He said he would represent BNP in the House Committee, which will look after the housing and other facilities of the MPs. bdn
